The primary duty of this position will consist of performing data and business analytics (SQL), statistical programming (R / SAS / Python) and analyses, communicating with stakeholders and collaborators, and assuring the quality and integrity of the final products
Communicate and work daily with all members of the analytic team to develop feasibility and resource estimates for data analytic projects, and reports to the Manager of Analytics and Research.
Attending meetings and conferences, and incorporating innovations and efficiencies in big data analyses
Performing routine queries to ensure database quality and report on data quality issues to the analytic team. Communicate with the IRIS Registry’s data vendor to address any and all data quality problems.

Knowledge about data analytics, business analytics, statistics, public health research, and medical/clinical research study methodology
Knowledge and experience in data analysis, reporting and analytic software: SQL is essential (PostgreSQL, MSSQL, Redshift), along with SAS (and SAS/SQL), R, or Python/pandas
Knowledge about Linux command line
Knowledge and experience with version control such as git, Github, or Bitbucket
Knowledge of data visualization and presentation skills to effectively communicate data insights
Experience with relational databases and data lake environments, including AWS
Knowledge about clinical data registries
Knowledge about electronic health record databases and structures
Experience in facilitating and/or leading analytic projects, with project management skills
Experience with health services research or population health studies for data collection, analysis and interpretation
Excellent written communication skills
Ability to analyze problems and develop solutions
Interpersonal and managerial skills
Team management skills and ability to serve as leader for complex and cross-divisional efforts
Creative, analytic approach to issues
Clear expression of ideas and concerns orally and in writing
A. or B.S. required
Masters degree in public health, business analytics, data science, statistics, or epidemiology is a plus

Name: Office of the CAO | Reference Data, Operations Analyst
Description:
Job Description

 We are looking for leaders and problem solvers who are passionate about data and data management. The purpose of the Operations team within the Reference Data Product Management group is to manage daily operations of enterprise reference data systems and associated businesses processes. The role requires effective management of tactical, BAU activity, as well as longer term, more strategic projects to introduce product and process improvements. 

A successful candidate will be an experienced Operations Analyst who communicates and collaborates effectively, taking ownership and accountability for operational stability, issues, and ongoing improvements in their areas of focus. They will demonstrate a track record of success in a fast-paced production role, with the ability to contribute meaningfully to data-driven process improvements over time. The ability to work effectively with a wide range of stakeholders – front office customers, project managers, business analysts, and technologists is important.

Required Skills

 Primary Responsibilities:

Reporting to the Operations team, the Operations Analyst will be responsible for delivering robust reference data operations, with a focus on instrument master data, but also including other types of reference data such as party and EOD pricing data.



Follow and maintain a daily playbook of operational procedures and controls 

Capture all metadata feeding into an Incident Management program for all reference data issues
Work with front and back office stakeholders across the organization to triage and fix production issues Produce operational reports for team and management reviews on a regular basis
Work with technologists, project managers, and business analysts to deliver reference data system upgrades 


Qualifications:





3 or more years of professional experience in financial services, particularly operational / production roles in support of trading and investment activities, or of associate data
Working knowledge of financial products and instruments,
Ability to work effectively in a fast-paced environment with multiple stakeholders
Very strong attention to detail, with an interest in process design and automation
Strong analytical skills



Education: BA/BS Bachelor’s Degree (STEM degree preferred)

About CitadelCitadel is a global investment firm built around world-class talent, sound risk management, and innovative leading-edge technology. For a quarter of a century, Citadel’s hedge funds have delivered meaningful and measurable results to top-tier investors around the world, including sovereign wealth funds, public institutions, corporate pensions, endowments and foundations.

With an unparalleled ability to identify and execute on great ideas, Citadel’s team of more than 675 investment professionals, operating from offices including Chicago, New York, San Francisco, London, Hong Kong and Shanghai, deploy capital across all major asset classes, in all major financial markets.

Name: Sr Business Data Analyst
Description:
Are you interested in becoming part of a dynamic team that is looking to innovate and improve?Would you like to work for a company that has been rated by the BBJ (15 yrs) as one of the best places to work?Do you want to be part of a company that is committed to giving back to the community?Harvard Pilgrim Health Care is currently seeking a highly motivated individual to join our organization as Sr Business Data Analyst. This role will be responsible for completing complex business system and data analytic assignments in support of departmental objectives, functioning as a senior analytic and technical lead on a broad array of assignments.
This particular position will be responsible for Pharmacy Data Exchanges and Accumulators.WHAT YOU WILL BE DOING:


Perform business and data analytic functions in support of Pharmacy data exchanges and Accumulators, develop proposals for enhancements and resolution of program bug fixes working in collaboration with other analysts and stakeholders.Collaborate with internal business and external vendor constituents to conduct analytic assignments in support of requested business solution(s). Ensure that appropriate requirements, associated business rules and data standards, and technical specifications for requested solutions are documented. Develop design recommendations commensurate of requested solution, ensuring recommendations comply with corporate architectural standards and federal and state regulations and/or mandates pertaining to the privacy and security of HPHC’s core data assets. Facilitate review of design with governing committees. Ensure development and maintenance procedures are in place for technical documentation of production pharmacy data exchange programs (for internal and external constituents), as well as those of external Pharmacy Benefit Managers and other business associates (i.e., CMS) needed to administer and monitor existing exchange relationships and conduct impact analyses of proposed changes to production environment.Plan, develop and implement solution designs of significant scope and complexity. Solutions may include application or extract program code, production reports and analytic finding reports. Independently develop solutions of considerable scope and complexity. Lead teams of junior analysts to fulfill components of solutions with significant scope and complexity. Lead quality assurance (QA) and user acceptance testing planning for developed solutions, and participates with business requestors in their user acceptance testing once QA testing is successfully completed. Develop test strategies, plans, and scripts and executes test procedures to ensure compliance of developed solution with documented specifications. Report test results to project stakeholders. Deliver training programs for IT and business personnel to ensure these standards, policies and procedures are well understood and adhered to by HPHC staff in accordance with regulatory requirements.
WHAT YOU NEED:


MA/MBA/MS or equivalent, plus 5 years experience, including a minimum of 3 years in health care data warehouse environment. Superior analytic problem-solving skills, including business process and data analytics. 

Data knowledge in finance or clinical side of insurance business; demonstrated ability to develop and deliver data analytic solutions of a complex nature. 

Demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously. Strong organizational skills, and the ability to prioritize multiple concurrent tasks. Strong verbal and written communication skills as well as negotiation skills. Team player, committed to quality process and outcomes. Demonstrated ability to lead teams and mentor junior data analysts. 

Proficient with PC’s; expertise in MS Office (MS Access, Word, Excel, Power Point, Visio, MS Project); sophisticated technical skills in SAS and SQL programming languages; Demonstrated understanding of principles of data modeling; Extract Transform Load (ETL) specifications; experience in database systems (Teradata, Oracle), as well as end-user analytic tools like MicroStrategy Web; Experience in MicroStrategy Web report development, understanding of its architecture and schema objects; Previous experience with documenting requirements, use cases, test cases, success criteria; Experience in Master Data Management. Ability to learn new technologies and applications quickly.
WHAT MAKES US STAND OUT
Work-Life-Flexibility 

Paid volunteer time off (up to 3 days annually) 

Open vacation 

Annual Mini-Grant of $500 donated to a non-profit organization of the employee’s choice 

Educational Reimbursement
Working EnvironmentNormal office working conditions. Must have the ability to travel between HPHC locations as required by the position.

Name: Data Center Support Analyst
Description:
*job details:**

*job description**
job summary:responsibilities:Responsibilities:
Perform tasks specific to the shift by following set procedures and work instructions to meet predetermined service level objectives.
Utilizing monitoring tools in place today, perform monitoring activities of system messages and alerts and escalate according to documented procedures.

Must be well organized and demonstrate the ability to follow instructions with attention to detail

Review and analyze source data and ensure data accuracy and integrity

Name: Senior Data Analyst for Product Growth
Description:
As a Senior Data Analyst for Product Growth, you will:
Lead all things data for a growth team in our Product organization
Identify the drivers of activation, monetization, and engagement
Analyze large, rich data sets
Improve our product which helps 100,000+ developers build and deliver software faster
Build our product and growth analytics practice
About Product Growth Analytics at CircleCIWhat you'll do:
Be a brilliant analyst: Turn business problems into research plans. Leverage data from the data lake, data warehouse, third parties, and source systems. Work confidently with clean and messy data. Aggregate, clean, and explore. Soundly use statistics and probability. Tell compelling stories. Build impactful visualizations. Present insights to peers and executives. Drive action and outcomes. Turn repetitive analyses into dashboards.
Lead analytics for a product team: Partner with product managers. Brainstorm ideas, experiments, hypotheses, and roadmaps. Collaborate to fully understand context, needs, vision, and outcomes. Ask smart questions. Set team goals. Define, document, monitor and forecast KPI. Perform root cause analyses on key metrics. Define requirements for developers to improve data instrumentation.
Understand our product and customers: Analyze product features, journeys, and life cycles. Drive conversion, engagement, and efficiency across our funnel. Focus on activation, monetization, engagement, and retention. Identify customer characteristics and behaviors. Improve segmenting and cohorting.
Leverage a growth toolkit: Define the models, paths, and loops of growth. Identify and prioritize opportunities for incremental improvements. Work in cycles of build, measure, and learn. Define, implement, and interpret A/B tests and other experiments. Educate stakeholders on statistical validity. 

Build a growth practice: Scale success. Celebrate fast failure. Mature from one-off tactics to repeatable processes. Define best practices. Embrace not just quantitative, but qualitative; not just analytics, but creative thinking. Define requirements for data engineering to improve data, automation and analytics capabilities. 
What we're looking for:


Six years total of analytics experience with three years in Product or Growth: At least six years of analytics experience in total. At least three of those years in an analytics role specifically focused on product or growth.
Experience at a high-growth company: Analytics experience with high-growth businesses. Ideally, those with well-defined, product-enabled funnels and complex, high-volume customer flows.
Technical education: A bachelor's degree in a technical or quantitative field (e.g., Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering, Economics or Finance). A similar Master's degree is preferred.
Proficiency across analytics tools: Deep experience with analytical SQL queries (e.g., inner/left/right joins, CTEs, and window functions). Some experience with scripting within a notebook environment, preferably using Python, Pandas, and Jupyter. A desire to grow your modeling, machine-learning, and data-science skills. Familiarity with basic statistics (e.g., distributions, experiments, significance testing, and linear regression). Experience with a major analytics/visualization platform (e.g., Tableau or Looker). 

Proficiency across growth tools: Productive with growth tools. Specifically a product or events analytics platform (e.g., Google Analytics, Amplitude, Segment) and an AB testing tool (e.g., Optimizely, VWO). 
Bonus Points!
Passion for data, discover, and problem-solving
Curious; confident; open to questioning assumptions and being questioned.
Effective communicator across technical and business audiences. Able to manage stakeholder expectations and work with hands-on executives.
Entrepreneurial; fast-moving; able to balance vision and execution; and not easily discouraged. Instinct for value, and focused on the incremental.

Description:
Provides support to the organization in regards to the processing and validation of various Pharmaceutical data sources, Speciality Pharma (SP) data utilized by field and home office personnel.  Must have extensive experience with Specialty Pharma (SP) data packages and the pharmaceutical sales process Must be organized and have the ability to present themselves to others Competent in MS Excel, PowerPoint and Access and familiar with data warehouse environments. Experience with system integrations/change management BS/MS degree in computer science or related discipline. 3-4 years of relevant experience in software development, preferably in distributed computing environments or big data platforms.

 Duties

Job Title

Business Analyst III (Data Governance)

Job Summary

The Business Analyst III is a key contributor to the TMNAS Data Governance effort. As such, the Business Analyst III is expected to leverage a broad knowledge of data governance and stewardship concepts in order to identify improvement opportunities (and propose solutions) based on insightful quantitative and qualitative analysis. The Business Analyst III should also have exceptional interpersonal and communication skills, in order to build and sustain relationships and lines of communication with key business and IT stakeholders, and to identify and partner with influential subject matter experts in order to drive measurably successful outcomes.

Job Responsibilities

• Provides quantitative and qualitative data and metadata analysis on programs, projects, sub-projects, and issues, as assigned

• Works with stakeholders to understand, prioritize, and document business and technical needs, and to ensure alignment with DG strategy

• Partners with architects and developers to infuse DG considerations into architectural planning and design

• Evangelizes DG strategy and promotes DG principles, policies, and best practices

• Establishes Data standards, creates critical DG artifacts and monitors compliance of standards

• Establishes KPIs for periodic measurement and reporting to the management team.

• Have innovation mindset and constantly strives to improve the Governance processes and KPIs

• Performs special projects and other duties as may be assigned

• Complies with proper internal controls as necessary to conduct job functions and/or carry out responsibilities and/or administrative activities at the Company

Qualifications

Degree / Licenses and Professional Certifications

• Bachelor’s Degree (preferably in Business, MIS, Computer Science or Mathematics) or equivalent experience required

Experience

• 5+ years of relevant experience

• Experience with SQL query-writing and BI tools such as Business Objects, Cognos, SSRS, etc.

• Significant experience with Data Governance / Metadata Management toolsets such as Informatica Axon/EDC or Collibra Data Center Governance is strongly preferred

• Experience with Informatica Data Quality (IDQ) is helpful

Competencies

• Broad working knowledge of data governance and data stewardship

• Deep appreciation of the need for data governance, as well as a solid understanding of how to apply DG tools and techniques to ensure business and project compliance with DG principles, policies, and practices

• Demonstrated ability to generate quantitative and qualitative analysis; especially data and metadata analysis

• Demonstrated problem solving, collaboration, and analytical skills

• Proven ability to establish and maintain effective working relationships with various levels of IT management, staff and business stakeholders

• Superior attention to detail

Knowledge

• Knowledge of Property & Casualty Insurance terminologies and processes is preferred

• Knowledge of Microsoft Office products (Visio, Excel, Word, PowerPoint, and Access)

• Knowledge of Business Process Management

• Knowledge of approaches, tools, and techniques for design and development of paper-based and online technical reference documentation, guidelines, standards, procedures, processes, applications, etc.

Skills

• Excellent interpersonal and communication skills (written and verbal)

• Strong customer service orientation (responsive, consultative, collaborative and accurate)

Abilities

• Ability to translate a deep understanding of the company’s value proposition—and of how data is used by TMNA’s various companies—into insightful quantitative and qualitative analysis

• Ability to work with business and IT stakeholders to help define, prioritize, document, validate and align data requirements with DG strategy

• Ability to leverage strong subject matter expertise related to business-process and data-usage, in order to collaborate with business and IT stakeholders and lead analysis projects and sub-projects as assigned

• Ability to juggle multiple, competing, frequently changing time-sensitive deadlines and priorities

In order to remain competitive we must attract, develop, motivate, and retain the most qualified employees regardless of age, color, race, religion, gender, disability, national or ethnic origin, family circumstances, life experiences, marital status, military status, sexual orientation and/or any other status protected by law.

Name: Data Analyst
Description:
Data Analyst



Location



Long Island City



Project Name



Department of Health and Mental Hygiene (DOHMH)



Employment Status



full-time




Apply NowCompany Overview

With an annual budget of $1.6 billion and more than 6,000 employees throughout the five boroughs, the New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene (NYC DOHMH) is one of the largest public health agencies in the world, serving 8 million New Yorkers from diverse ethnic and cultural backgrounds. With over 200 years of leadership in the field, we're also one of our nation's oldest public health agencies. The challenges we face range from obesity, diabetes and heart disease to HIV/AIDS, tobacco addiction and substance abuse, and the threat of bioterrorism. We're tackling these issues with innovative policies and programs and getting exceptional results, but our work is never finished. The breadth of our innovative programs provides the widest range of choices for every member of our team.

Program Overview

The Division of Disease Control (DDC) at the New York City (NYC) Department of Health and Mental Hygiene (DOHMH) is responsible for the identification, surveillance, treatment, control and prevention of infectious diseases in NYC. The Division is composed of six bureaus: Bureau of Communicable Disease Control, Bureau of HIV/AIDS, Bureau of Immunization, Bureau of Sexually Transmitted Disease Control, Bureau of Tuberculosis Control and the Public Health Laboratory. Surveillance teams across the DDC bureaus collectively monitor and investigate over 90 reportable infectious diseases to detect, characterize, and respond to threats.

DDC continuously enhances its electronic systems in order to improve completeness of data and respond to emergent infectious agent threats (e.g., Zika virus, Ebola). More recently, DDC has embarked on an initiative to improve the interoperability of its surveillance informatics infrastructure by leveraging national health data standards. This will facilitate exchange with partners including healthcare providers, laboratories, health information exchanges (HIEs) such as the regional health information organizations (RHIOs), and other government agencies.

Position Summary

The person hired for this position will support innovative public health informatics projects and build infrastructure for more meaningful use of electronic health information. They will become one of DDC’s top subject matter experts on quality of NYC surveillance data. This person will advise DOHMH stakeholders to ensure that data quality issues are identified, documented, and resolved. Additionally, they will gain more knowledge of DOHMH surveillance by assisting in project coordination, management and evaluation as necessary.

The selected candidate will be an employee of Public Health Solutions (PHS), a non-profit organization that is the fiscal manager for DOHMH. This position is a 2 year position, paid for by 90/10 Health Information Technology for Economic and Clinical Health Act funding.

Job description

The selected candidate’s responsibilities will include but not be limited to:


Develop and implement automated or semi-automated scripts to analyze data quality and clean, enrich, map, and transform data to surveillance SME’s specifications.

Perform quality assurance and evaluate the completeness and accuracy of data received through electronic laboratory results and/or electronic case reporting.

Conduct root cause analyses to identify and remediate workflow and technology-related issues that result in loss of data quality.

Develop dashboards, visualizations, and presentations to summarize and explain data quality issues.

Advise stakeholders on data-related considerations in planning for: 1) technology, e.g., pipelines to move data into the surveillance system; and 2) operations, e.g., onboarding healthcare providers to health information exchange with NYC DOHMH.

Contribute to project coordination, management, and evaluation with a lens for data quality.

Qualifications:


Bachelor’s Degree

Demonstrated skill in descriptive analysis of “raw” data using SAS, SQL, R, and/or Python

Familiarity with HL7 and/or XML

Experience with public health, business intelligence, or informatics

Preferred Skills:


Master’s degree from an accredited college or university with a specialization or equivalent experience in an appropriate field of public health, computer science, or informatics

Experience and/or academic work in public health surveillance or quantitative analysis

Experience with HL7 Clinical Document Architecture (CDA) and/or Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources (FHIR)

Experience deploying automated data processing scripts into production environments

Excellent oral and written communication skills

Highly organized, able to manage multiple simultaneous projects

Strong interpersonal communication and time management skills with attention to detail

PHS is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and encourages applications from women, people of color, persons with disabilities, lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender individuals, and veterans

Name: Data Analyst
Description:
Data Analyst Role and Responsibilities Organizational Role: The Data Analyst supports the studio Marketing, Production and Business leaders achieving our business goals by:
initiating quantitative analyses across customer, market, pricing and behavioral data to enable studio leaders to make informed decisions;
translate data into actionable insights based on product and service strategic priorities to drive business impact, optimize the player journey and direct process improvement; 
provide data-driven decision-making support to direct prioritization of strategic projects including: customer acquisition, engagement/monetization initiatives and growth of LTV (lifetime value) based on behavioral insights, activity profiles, purchasing data and trend analysis that offers predictive insights to guide increased performance within key KPIs 
In a fast-growing industry characterized by rapid change and a highly competitive business environment the analyst’s priority is to aid management in making data-driven decisions quickly and efficiently to drive profitable growth. Further, the Data Analyst provides reporting and performance monitoring to track key performance indicators (KPIs) and trends to proactively identify actionable opportunities and emerging threats to the business.The Data Analyst is expected to design and execute processes, reporting, and modeling that can scale to support studio growth. Critical to the success of the studio, the Data Analyst builds models to inform sales forecasts, projections for new product introductions, pricing and promotional returns. Additionally, the Data Analyst is able to create an infrastructure within the data warehouse that serves on-demand and ongoing data analysis and queries including agile access to structure and service a wide variety of requests to inform decisions and impact performance KPIs within a short turnaround (days) - offering ease of access to support a fast-paced business.As the Data Analyst you will grow and maintain the reporting suite as needed to maximize business impact – from daily to quarterly. You will provide variance reports and glean competitor insights. This function aids in accelerating business growth through identification of levers and bottlenecks within the framework of an ever-changing live service ecosystem. Above all, your work will impact the path the studio takes to prepare for the future and to help it adapt to ongoing shifts in the market.What You Will DoMarketing Reporting & Analysis
Support the VP, Marketing and Business leaders in annual sales/acquisition forecasting and budgeting process by supplying historical data, market analysis data insights and competitive data along with industry trend/data reports as input into production of annual forecasts for Marketing Spend, Revenue, Acquisition, Churn, ARPU and LTV calculation
Track and analyze components of programs that do/do not perform in terms of ROI to provide data-driven guidance to business owners and decision makers
Review and advise VP Marketing and Studio Leaders on insights and monthly performance; support production of monthly performance summary for Investors
Partner with marketing to build, track and trend behavioral insights by player profile to build/test models enabling proactive outreach to support long-term player retention.
Provide analysis and insights to executives to identify variances between actual and expected results and identify causal relationships; to enable performance improvements
Support development of detailed Player Performance Dashboards, drive trend analysis and leverage A/B Testing and structure read-outs to initiate correlation analysis via Machine Learning tools; identify behavioral profiles which correlate to LTV.
Analyze marketing performance by channel including organic vs. paid acquisition volume, churn percentage, spend conversion, ARPU, referral and LTV for optimization
 Business Planning & Analysis 
Address ad hoc financial/behavioral and player segment analysis requests and inquiries
Support curation of industry insights and data as well as Competitor data and trends
Support analysis for the Global Marketing strategy based on segmentation and global channel optimization strategy including channel efficiency and pricing optimization
Lead analysis of competitive pricing, MTX bundling, and live service content strategy (events, expansions, updates), to educate leadership on competitors’ position and guide recommendations to improve studio position in the market
Partner with Marketing and Platform/Web team to lead efforts on providing data-driven insights for pathing efficiency and process improvements in player navigation of Store, Cart and website flow for top ten reasons that drive player visits to the site.

You are the person who will educate management on the power of data driven insights and be material in the growth of the business.You will take ownership of the accuracy, reliability and, relevance of the marketing/customer data and player behavioral analysis; and articulate root causes and drivers of changes in performance impacting the business.Experienced in Data Analysis for a Competitive Consumer Industry
3-5 years of business and marketing data analytics role and/or consulting data analytics experience for a competitive consumer industry

Name: Sr. Data Analyst
Description:
Who We Are

At MassMutual, we help millions of people find financial freedom, offer financial protection, and plan for the future. Were passionate about helping millions of people find financial freedom and this passion has driven our approach to developing meaningful experiences for our customers. We do this by building trust with our customers by being knowledgeable problem solvers and prioritize their needs above all else. We Live Mutual. MassMutual was named a Top Place to Work in 2019 according to The Boston Globe and No. 84 on the Fortune 500 list of largest companies.

Meet the Team Data Analytics

It is an exciting time at MassMutual! MassMutual is going through a Digital Transformation, continuing to be a leading customer-centric company. The Data Analytics team, part of MassMutuals new Enterprise Technology Experience organization, is comprised of highly skilled, collaborative problem solvers who are motivated to create innovative solutions that exceed the changing needs of our customers and move MassMutual and the industry forward. The team culture is collaborative, cross-functional, and uses old and new technologies combined with the work/life balance.

Current Initiatives:

·Enterprise-wide transition to a unified and governed strategic BI Platform

·Expansion of Digital Operations footprint, and growing need for access to actionable data insights

·Revitalization of analytics and reporting applications to support changing industry needs and expectations

The Opportunity

Are you highly analytical and like to solve complex problems? Would you describe yourself as a strong collaborative leader? Would you want to be part of a team that encourages your growth, supports your ambitions, and makes it a priority for you to reach your goals? If yes ... keep reading, this opportunity is for you!

Job Description

To continue our digital transformation, we are looking for a strategic thinker and strong analytical mind to join the Data Analytics team that is tasked with implementing an enterprise strategy to enable seamless integration of analytics best practices and standards to business processes. The Sr. Data Analyst is a critical role to enabling stakeholders and partners to harness the power of their data for decision making. This role will be responsible to work directly with stakeholders, product managers, and engineering teams to understand business objectives/ goals. The Sr. Data Analyst will explore the data, ensuring quality and accuracy, and present it in easily consumable format for the business to use in their decision making process.

Objectives and Responsibilities

·Lead discussions with partner teams to elicit, define, and understand objectives, goals, and desired insights

·Provide subject matter expertise on the data needs for project deliveries, scope, acceptance, installation and deployment.

·Interpret data, analyze results using statistical techniques and provide ongoing reports

·Develop and implement databases, data collection systems, data analytics and other strategies that optimize statistical efficiency and quality

·Acquire data from primary or secondary data sources and maintain databases/data systems

·Identify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets

·Filter and clean data to locate and correct code problems

·Work with management to prioritize business and information needs

·Locate and define new process improvement opportunities

·Work with data partners to develop/ enhance data to gain required insights

·Design and develop dashboards and reports to visualize analysis results using BI tools

·Contribute to the design, development and completion of project deliverables.

Qualifications

Bachelors degree or equivalent in Information Technology, Computer Science, CIS, Engineering, or Math

7+ years proven working experience as a data analyst or business data analyst

Technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, data mining and segmentation techniques

Strong knowledge of and experience with BI Solutions (Micro Strategy, Looker, Tableau), databases (SQL), programming (Python, XML, JavaScript, or ETL frameworks)

Knowledge of statistics and experience analyzing datasets

Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy

Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings

Must be comfortable working with large amounts of data

Ability to work individually and in a team-oriented, collaborative environment

Ability to handle multiple tasks delivering under the Agile methodology

Strong written and verbal communication skills

Authorized to work in the United States without sponsorship now or in the future

Preferred Qualifications

10+ years proven working experience as a data analyst or business data analyst

Apply NowDermalogica Global Data Analyst

Dermalogica continues to dominate the professional skin care industry with distribution in over 90 countries. Known worldwide as the premiere Skin Therapist’s choice for offering the most respected professional skin care line, we are also recognized for our renowned postgraduate education.

Our entrepreneurial spirit, hands-on environment and fast-paced culture encourages employees to be their best, bringing innovative solutions to reach the skin care professional and consumer. We are highly energetic, passionate, and results-oriented. You will find that Dermalogica is a very special place, with tremendous opportunities ahead for us, all building upon a record of achievement.

In 2015 Dermalogica was acquired by Unilever, one of the world’s largest and most successful consumer goods companies. Whilst Dermalogica continues to operate as a stand-alone entrepreneurial business, we now have an enviable access to cutting edge capabilities and resources to help us win in our markets.

Dermalogica has a global turnover of in of +$250m with a healthy operating margin. The challenge is to build on the legacy of our brand, our experienced team and our industry leading education to deliver profitable growth. One of the key elements for our success, and critical for our growth, is bringing in the right people to join our team. We invite you to come and make a difference and grow your career with the global leader in skin care.

***************************************************

Dermalogica is seeking a talented Data Analyst

General Description:

This role is based in our headquarters in Carson, California. We need to empower people across the business with information as well as supporting our entrepreneurial culture through building, testing and iterating hypotheses. To do that we need people with analytical expertise and the motivation to apply it to prestige skin care.

Our analytics agenda is moving at pace and this role is key to continuing to move us towards our goal to be industry leading. We have work to do to; establish a standard data model within a future proofed environment, continue to develop analytic tools across chosen BI software and to build analytical skills across the business.

The right person for this role demonstrates a passion and curiosity in identifying and interpreting trends within complex data sets to deliver actionable insights as well as supporting and driving efficiencies in our correct processes. This role reports through the finance function to the Global Information and Analytics Manager but is broader in scope than simply financial/sales analytics.

Key Job Accountabilities:

Database Administration/Process Improvement


Defines business intelligence requirements for analytics projects and data requests, working with key stakeholders to meet the requirements for executive management such as incorporating new data sources into existing databases to improve our analytical capabilities.

Collaborate with the IT department to advise evaluate databases, database tools, and database software standards and procedures to drive efficiencies. 

Seek opportunities to improve performance of our current monthly processes by identifying time and resource savings and implementing them. 

Requirement to support current monthly processes as required, including working in Adaptive insights and Tableau, essential skill requirement to develop system related knowledge of Adaptive Insights.

Follows best practices in business intelligence, data integrity, maintenance including data validation between database tables and systems.

Analytics Development


Ensure the different corporate functions have the standard analytical tools to be self-sufficient in performance management. 

Embed user friendly analytical tools for the team, which includes monitoring usage, shutting off what is not used, and having all workbooks accessible to the users in the proper formats.

Review current distribution of reports in Excel and determine what can be simplified/automated in Tableau.

Demonstrate ability to synthesize data and focus on key, relevant business insights. Ability to effectively communicate insights and recommendations that contribute to the development of business driving strategies.

Experience and Competencies Required:


Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Business, Finance or Information Management or another related field.

Strong knowledge of SQL and SQL databases advantageous. 

Experience with Adaptive Insights and data imports would be beneficial. 

Strong leadership skills (planning, communication, relationship building, influencing)

Expert experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI. 

Experience using data manipulation tools (such as Alteryx) and building visualizations using large datasets and multiple data sources. 

Excellent initiative and follow-up skills, and ability to carry out a variety of responsibilities.

Fast learner for fast-paced work environment.

Demonstrate an analytical mindset, enjoy problem solving and understand how to ask the right questions to deliver solution focused outcomes.

Self-motivated, detail-oriented, learn autonomously, and highly organized

Specific tasks include: Mining large and complex databases and maintaining detailed data dictionaries; Obtaining and managing publically available databases; Cleaning data; Performing descriptive and statistical analyses; writing and generating reports.

Name: Data Analyst
Description:
Data Analyst
 

  Job DetailsLevel ExperiencedJob Location Home Office - , Position Type Full TimeEducation Level BachelorsSalary Range UndisclosedTravel Percentage NegligibleJob Shift DayJob Category EngineeringDescription Operational Data & Analytics is Catasys’ core system for instrumentation and analytical reporting for business-critical measures. You will drive a culture of rigorous, evidence-based decision making to answer the question “Do we think this is true? Or do we know?”

As a Data Analyst, you will drive innovation, growth, and contribute to the company’s ability to scale. Your work continually broadens access to reliable, accurate, and timely data to improve decision making. You will transform data into insights, leading to faster and more extensive exploratory analysis and quicker action based on evidence. Your insights will help grow the business by accelerating sales and customer expansion cycles, reinforcing Catasys’ position as an industry leader in data and analytics. You excel at synthesize and communicate complex concepts and analyses in easy to understand ways.

Responsibilities



	Dive into data to predict and quantify user behavior: our members, Care Team, and network providers. 

Find actionable strategic insights through funnels, cohort analyses, user segmentation, retention analyses and regression models to help us grow our products.

Data storytelling: quantify user journeys to help identify opportunities to improve member outcomes and team productivity.

Become a Catasys subject matter expert to understand and anticipate the data needs of customers, Product, User Experience, and internal stakeholders.

Translate high-priority business problems to solve into concise measures.

Lead the Analytics Center of Excellence: a cross-functional team of Data Champions within the organization.

Drive a culture of analytical rigor and transparency, and shared understanding of measures

Work both collaboratively and autonomously.

Define KPIs, build automated dashboards, reports, and models to help teams make faster better decisions.

Work with engineering and product to implement, quality assurance, and monitor our logging and metrics.

Requirements



	Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, math, economics, statistics, or other quantitative fields

2+ years’ experience with PowerBI DAX Programming

Expertise performing quantitative analysis

Excellent communication and presentation skills: you understand your audience and how to effectively present information to diverse stakeholders

Strong understanding of statistical methods and applications (A/B testing, probability, regression)

Preferred Qualifications



	Prior experience in healthcare and FHIR data modeling a plus

At least 2 years of experience with SQL (BigQuery and MySQL is a plus)

Experience working with very large data sets and distributed computing (Hive/Hadoop/MapReduce)

Familiarity with web analytics tools, e.g. Google Analytics, Azure Application Insights

Experience with marketing analytics (e.g. Attribution/Forecasting)

Familiarity with R or Python is a plus

All work from home opportunities require:



	A quiet, private, distraction-free home office work environment

A reliable high-speed internet connection (cable, DSL or fiber) with speeds of at least 10Mbps download and 5Mbps upload

Willingness to do constant sedentary work

Discipline to work from home while following a set schedule

Background check clearance



Qualifications Catasys is making a positive impact on people’s lives every day. We use predictive analytics to identify health plan members with unaddressed behavioral health conditions that worsen chronic disease, then engage, support and guide these members to better health with a personalized, human-centered approach. This has led us to where we are today: growing fast and saving lives as we do.

To support our explosive growth, we’re looking for compassionate, hard-working people-lovers to join our team. If innovating in the field of patient care is something you’re passionate about, we encourage you to join our mission to improve the health and save the lives of as many people as possible.

Impact lives in so many ways

You'll be an integral part in supporting people coping with their unique life challenges. Every member of the Catasys team contributes to accomplishing our goals and upholding our people-centric values.

The new face of mental health

Our model is research-based, and we are invested in staying on the leading edge of treatment. You'll help us break down barriers and stigmas associated with mental health.

Career options

Our ongoing strong growth and evolution, we are looking for people who want to do their best at work. Join our team and take your career to the next level with Catasys. We are committed to promoting from within.

Excellent compensation

In addition to a competitive wage, we offer comprehensive benefits including medical, dental and vision insurance; a 401(k) plan; paid holiday, vacation and sick time; flexible spending accounts; Basic Life/AD&D, Employee Assistance Program and Travel Assistance Program and more.

Catasys is an equal opportunity employer. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or protected veteran status

Name: Data Analyst
Description:
We are looking for a high-performing Data Analyst to join our analytics practice. As an analyst, you will play an integral part of the team and work directly with our clients to provide best-in-class analytics solutions and data-driven insights. This role requires analytical curiosity and strong SQL skills, but is not a DBA or ETL developer role.
 
Key Responsibilities:

 



Create meaningful business insights out of customer, transactional, and other behavioral data.
Conduct both short- and long-term custom analytics projects, design analysis plans, and prepare client deliverables.
Query large databases and other data sources using SQL programming languages.
Support BI reporting development and CRM targeting efforts.
Identify meaningful business insights out of queried data and prepare summary findings for both internal and external stakeholders.
Build relationships and communicate regularly with external clients.




Experience & Skills:

 



Excellent data analytic skills. Your analytical thinking is far more important than technical skills
Curiosity when analyzing data. Documented history of thinking outside the box and creating novel solutions.
Analytic agility. Ability to change analysis direction based on interim findings.
Evidence of experience working with multiple, large datasets/warehouses, and ability to integrate and extract from such datasets using relevant programs and coding.
Experience using SQL to analyze customer level data, such as POS/transactional or weblog clickstream data.
Aptitude for refining informal analytic, reporting or query requirements to help move beyond the simple ask and surface the underlying “why”.
Strong Excel skills. Experience and familiarity with a wide variety of Excel functions and features (well beyond pivot tables).



Desired Qualifications:





Excellent communication skills. Experience explaining technical findings to non-technical audiences.
Experience using programming languages such as R or Python to extract, manipulate, and analyze customer data is a strong plus. 
Statistical analysis experience is a plus: regression modeling, decision trees, clustering, etc.
BS or MS in Statistics, Computer Science, Mathematics, Applied Economics, Biostatistics or a field involving experimental design, probabilities and quantitative analysis.
1-3 years of relevant experience.
Must be authorized to legally work in the United States without restrictions or need for a work visa.




Why Work at Centriam?

 



Small analytics company focused on delivering excellence and value to our clients by providing high quality analytical and data-driven solutions.
Fun & collaborative culture; you will wear many hats and play an integral part in projects.
Exposure to a wide variety of data analytics, cloud, and open source technologies.

401k with generous match, vested immediately.
Free drinks, coffee, beer, and snacks.

Name: Senior Data Analyst for Product Growth
Description:
As a Senior Data Analyst for Product Growth, you will:
Lead all things data for a growth team in our Product organization
Identify the drivers of activation, monetization, and engagement
Analyze large, rich data sets
Improve our product which helps 100,000+ developers build and deliver software faster
Build our product and growth analytics practice
About Product Growth Analytics at CircleCIWhat you'll do:
Be a brilliant analyst: Turn business problems into research plans. Leverage data from the data lake, data warehouse, third parties, and source systems. Work confidently with clean and messy data. Aggregate, clean, and explore. Soundly use statistics and probability. Tell compelling stories. Build impactful visualizations. Present insights to peers and executives. Drive action and outcomes. Turn repetitive analyses into dashboards.
Lead analytics for a product team: Partner with product managers. Brainstorm ideas, experiments, hypotheses, and roadmaps. Collaborate to fully understand context, needs, vision, and outcomes. Ask smart questions. Set team goals. Define, document, monitor and forecast KPI. Perform root cause analyses on key metrics. Define requirements for developers to improve data instrumentation.
Understand our product and customers: Analyze product features, journeys, and life cycles. Drive conversion, engagement, and efficiency across our funnel. Focus on activation, monetization, engagement, and retention. Identify customer characteristics and behaviors. Improve segmenting and cohorting.
Leverage a growth toolkit: Define the models, paths, and loops of growth. Identify and prioritize opportunities for incremental improvements. Work in cycles of build, measure, and learn. Define, implement, and interpret A/B tests and other experiments. Educate stakeholders on statistical validity. 

Build a growth practice: Scale success. Celebrate fast failure. Mature from one-off tactics to repeatable processes. Define best practices. Embrace not just quantitative, but qualitative; not just analytics, but creative thinking. Define requirements for data engineering to improve data, automation and analytics capabilities. 
What we're looking for:


Six years total of analytics experience with three years in Product or Growth: At least six years of analytics experience in total. At least three of those years in an analytics role specifically focused on product or growth.
Experience at a high-growth company: Analytics experience with high-growth businesses. Ideally, those with well-defined, product-enabled funnels and complex, high-volume customer flows.
Technical education: A bachelor's degree in a technical or quantitative field (e.g., Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering, Economics or Finance). A similar Master's degree is preferred.
Proficiency across analytics tools: Deep experience with analytical SQL queries (e.g., inner/left/right joins, CTEs, and window functions). Some experience with scripting within a notebook environment, preferably using Python, Pandas, and Jupyter. A desire to grow your modeling, machine-learning, and data-science skills. Familiarity with basic statistics (e.g., distributions, experiments, significance testing, and linear regression). Experience with a major analytics/visualization platform (e.g., Tableau or Looker). 

Proficiency across growth tools: Productive with growth tools. Specifically a product or events analytics platform (e.g., Google Analytics, Amplitude, Segment) and an AB testing tool (e.g., Optimizely, VWO). 
Bonus Points!
Passion for data, discover, and problem-solving
Curious; confident; open to questioning assumptions and being questioned.
Effective communicator across technical and business audiences. Able to manage stakeholder expectations and work with hands-on executives.
Entrepreneurial; fast-moving; able to balance vision and execution; and not easily discouraged. Instinct for value, and focused on the incremental.
How To applyAbout CircleCI

Name: Data Analyst
Description:
Data Analyst


Reports to: VP of Data Operations

Location: Boston, MA

Comlinkdata is seeking a quantitative, critical thinker with an insatiable curiosity to join the Data Operations team as a Data Analyst. The Data Operations team is a critical component of Comlinkdata. They ensure our data is validated, the platform is working correctly and they explore opportunities to leverage new data sets to improve and create new products.

The Data Analyst will support the Data Operations team by gathering data, analyzing ad hoc reports, providing quality assurance and working jointly with the Client Services team to investigate data abnormalities. This candidate should be interested in working with large data sets in an “R&D skunkworks,” product development environment.

Responsibilities

Including, but not limited to:


Analyze and interpret data using statistical and business models
Identify correlations and trends in data, in addition to internal and external factors that could affect the results of our information
Provide input on how to integrate additional data sets from independent sources we can use to leverage our existing data
Collaborate with colleagues on ad hoc projects within the data science teams (Data ops and R&D)
Validate data daily using external data and research (quantitative and qualitative)
Troubleshoot data issues

Candidate Profile

Required Skills


3-5 years of work experience (or comparable educational experience) in quantitative analysis
Proficient in Excel and SQL
Experience business and statistical modeling
Strong critical thinking and problem solving skills
Creative and independent thinker with a desire to learn new technical skills
Success at working on cross-functional teams to meet a common goal
Self-starter with a high sense of urgency
Ability to prioritize in a multitask environment

Desired Skills


Knowledge of PYTHON and VB a plus (or willing to learn)
Knowledge of R, S-Plus, SAS, Stata, Gauss or Matlab a plus (or willing to learn)

Please submit a resume and cover letter to joinus@comlinkdata.com.

At this time, Comlinkdata will not sponsor a new applicant for employment sponsorship for this position.

About Comlinkdata

Comlinkdata is a 9-year-old, Boston based, analytics company that specializes in providing valuable insight across the telecom industry. It’s customers have come to rely on and respect the high quality of our data and the depth of our analysis to make daily tactical decisions and validate short and long-term strategic goals. Built on a culture of collaboration and innovation and using leading technology and unique data sources, the team unlocks critical consumer behavior used to analyze and predict market trends.

Name: Data Analyst
Description:
GCC Technologies, founded in 1997 with headquarters in Oakland, Maryland, is a fast growing service-disabled Veteran owned Small Business and HUBZone company with an outstanding record of performance providing more effective and efficient acquisition, business process, administrative and security services to multiple federal agencies. GCC was recently ISO certified under ISO 9001:2015.

Job Description--General Responsibilities:

The Data Analyst works as a member of the recruitment marketing team and assist with statistical reporting for all aspects of the Department’s national recruitment efforts. Must have an active Secret Clearance to be considered!!!! Job Description--Essential Functions:

The Data Analyst reports to the HR/REE Deputy Office Director. S/he works provides a wide variety of technical support services to the HR/REE staff. The responsibilities of the position include, but are not limited to the following:


Provide reports derived for statistical analysis of hiring and onboarding data from the HR/REE Tracking Application (REETA). 

S/he evaluates program functions and demographics, the implementation and effects of automated data processing, internet, and intranet procedures, and provides comprehensive reports to the Deputy Director and others in the office, as needed.

S/he coordinates with Bureau program and computer system managers in analysis of needs and management of data bases and automated systems for the Bureau of Human Resources.

S/he works closely with the Bureau’s systems administrator to maintain the REE Tracking Application (REETA), including maintaining user-defined system tables; add, modifying or inactivating letter/email templates; creating data entry templates for new programs and updating the server with current status/standing for applicants/candidates.

S/he works closely with the Bureau’s program and computer system managers to manage the office’s online application system (Gateway to State), including providing support to applicants and to system users within HR/REE as well as other bureau’s in the Department of State and serving as liaison between HR/REE and the system provider.

S/he prepare and presents reports of findings relevant to Recruitment program objectives, trends, demographic and results.


Preferred Experience:



S/he is experienced with Google Analytics, and works closely with the Marketing team to evaluate careers site data and prepares reports of findings relevant to audience, behavior, and acquisition.

S/he works closely with the Marketing team to evaluate the careers site customer satisfaction survey and develop recommendations to improve the user experience.

Advanced knowledge with power point and Tableau preferred but not required


Clearance: Secret

Education:



Bachelor's Degree, Additional years experience may be applied to degree.

Advanced education such as Master or JD counts as two years additional experience.

A minimum of one (1) year of relevant experience

10 years of overall general experience required.

Name: Business Analyst III - Data Governance
Description:
Business Analyst III - Data Governance

Job ID:1006405

 
Location:Bala Cynwyd, PA

 
Updated:March 9, 2020
 Duties

Job Title

Business Analyst III (Data Governance)

Job Summary

The Business Analyst III is a key contributor to the TMNAS Data Governance effort. As such, the Business Analyst III is expected to leverage a broad knowledge of data governance and stewardship concepts in order to identify improvement opportunities (and propose solutions) based on insightful quantitative and qualitative analysis. The Business Analyst III should also have exceptional interpersonal and communication skills, in order to build and sustain relationships and lines of communication with key business and IT stakeholders, and to identify and partner with influential subject matter experts in order to drive measurably successful outcomes.

Job Responsibilities

• Provides quantitative and qualitative data and metadata analysis on programs, projects, sub-projects, and issues, as assigned

• Works with stakeholders to understand, prioritize, and document business and technical needs, and to ensure alignment with DG strategy

• Partners with architects and developers to infuse DG considerations into architectural planning and design

• Evangelizes DG strategy and promotes DG principles, policies, and best practices

• Establishes Data standards, creates critical DG artifacts and monitors compliance of standards

• Establishes KPIs for periodic measurement and reporting to the management team.

• Have innovation mindset and constantly strives to improve the Governance processes and KPIs

• Performs special projects and other duties as may be assigned

• Complies with proper internal controls as necessary to conduct job functions and/or carry out responsibilities and/or administrative activities at the Company

Qualifications

Degree / Licenses and Professional Certifications

• Bachelor’s Degree (preferably in Business, MIS, Computer Science or Mathematics) or equivalent experience required

Experience

• 5+ years of relevant experience

• Experience with SQL query-writing and BI tools such as Business Objects, Cognos, SSRS, etc.

• Significant experience with Data Governance / Metadata Management toolsets such as Informatica Axon/EDC or Collibra Data Center Governance is strongly preferred

• Experience with Informatica Data Quality (IDQ) is helpful

Competencies

• Broad working knowledge of data governance and data stewardship

• Deep appreciation of the need for data governance, as well as a solid understanding of how to apply DG tools and techniques to ensure business and project compliance with DG principles, policies, and practices

• Demonstrated ability to generate quantitative and qualitative analysis; especially data and metadata analysis

• Demonstrated problem solving, collaboration, and analytical skills

• Proven ability to establish and maintain effective working relationships with various levels of IT management, staff and business stakeholders

• Superior attention to detail

Knowledge

• Knowledge of Property & Casualty Insurance terminologies and processes is preferred

• Knowledge of Microsoft Office products (Visio, Excel, Word, PowerPoint, and Access)

• Knowledge of Business Process Management

• Knowledge of approaches, tools, and techniques for design and development of paper-based and online technical reference documentation, guidelines, standards, procedures, processes, applications, etc.

Skills

• Excellent interpersonal and communication skills (written and verbal)

• Strong customer service orientation (responsive, consultative, collaborative and accurate)

Abilities

• Ability to translate a deep understanding of the company’s value proposition—and of how data is used by TMNA’s various companies—into insightful quantitative and qualitative analysis

• Ability to work with business and IT stakeholders to help define, prioritize, document, validate and align data requirements with DG strategy

• Ability to leverage strong subject matter expertise related to business-process and data-usage, in order to collaborate with business and IT stakeholders and lead analysis projects and sub-projects as assigned

• Ability to juggle multiple, competing, frequently changing time-sensitive deadlines and priorities

EEO Statement

Tokio Marine Group of Companies (including, but not limited to the Philadelphia Insurance Companies, Tokio Marine America, Inc., TMNA Services, LLC, TM Claims Service, Inc. and First Insurance Company of Hawaii, Ltd.) is an Equal Opportunity Employer. In order to remain competitive we must attract, develop, motivate, and retain the most qualified employees regardless of age, color, race, religion, gender, disability, national or ethnic origin, family circumstances, life experiences, marital status, military status, sexual orientation and/or any other status protected by law.

Name: Data Analyst
Description:
Position Objective:

Conduct data analysis and related functions in order to inform stakeholders, understand data trends, and tie data into business processes and objectives.

Duties and Responsibilities

Develop, update, and apply data models to generate reports and analysis to inform stakeholders.
Retrieve, validate, format, and organize a variety of data from many sources.
Conduct data analysis to answer standard or recurring inquiries and identify trends, correlation, and other relationships in data sets.
Work across various stakeholders to understand data trends, sources, and analysis goals and connect data to business processes to obtain a deeper understanding of potential considerations and assumptions.
Provide data integration by linking data from multiple sources to conduct organizational analysis.
Conduct detail oriented tasks and analysis projects independently with minimal supervision.
Create supporting materials for analysis projects (assumptions, briefings, handouts, written documents, user guides, etc.).
Development of metrics to identify trends in training and other integral data.

Basic Qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree in related field
At least four years of related experience in an office or professional setting
Secret Clearance

Minimum Qualifications:

Highly proficient in the MS Office Suite, particularly MS Excel.
Familiarity with software or tools used for business analytics, data analysis, and visualization such as Tableau, PowerPivot, PowerBI, Access, or Vizio.
Excellent data gathering and analytical skills.
Experience with data visualization methods and approaches.
Excellent oral and written communication skills.
Experience working with large data sets to distill information and present to all levels of organizational leadership.
Ability to interpret and analyze complex data, including sensitivity analyses, predictive analyses, and trends analyses.

This team is dedicated to providing our behavioral health customers with data driven information that provides insight and value in their clinical, financial and operational performance. As a part of our team, you will be involved with high level resources and will create actionable results for our customers. Our vision is that every healthcare decision will be powered by data in order to drive personalized, comprehensive care.

The responsibilities of the Data Analyst start from the initial project planning and progress to the analysis, design, implementation, testing, release and maintenance of our customer projects.

Name: Sr Business Data Analyst
Description:
Are you interested in becoming part of a dynamic team that is looking to innovate and improve?Would you like to work for a company that has been rated by the BBJ (15 yrs) as one of the best places to work?Do you want to be part of a company that is committed to giving back to the community?Harvard Pilgrim Health Care is currently seeking a highly motivated individual to join our organization as Sr Business Data Analyst. This role will be responsible for completing complex business system and data analytic assignments in support of departmental objectives, functioning as a senior analytic and technical lead on a broad array of assignments.
This particular position will be responsible for Pharmacy Data Exchanges and Accumulators.WHAT YOU WILL BE DOING:


Perform business and data analytic functions in support of Pharmacy data exchanges and Accumulators, develop proposals for enhancements and resolution of program bug fixes working in collaboration with other analysts and stakeholders.Collaborate with internal business and external vendor constituents to conduct analytic assignments in support of requested business solution(s). Ensure that appropriate requirements, associated business rules and data standards, and technical specifications for requested solutions are documented. Develop design recommendations commensurate of requested solution, ensuring recommendations comply with corporate architectural standards and federal and state regulations and/or mandates pertaining to the privacy and security of HPHC’s core data assets. Facilitate review of design with governing committees. Ensure development and maintenance procedures are in place for technical documentation of production pharmacy data exchange programs (for internal and external constituents), as well as those of external Pharmacy Benefit Managers and other business associates (i.e., CMS) needed to administer and monitor existing exchange relationships and conduct impact analyses of proposed changes to production environment.Plan, develop and implement solution designs of significant scope and complexity. Solutions may include application or extract program code, production reports and analytic finding reports. Independently develop solutions of considerable scope and complexity. Lead teams of junior analysts to fulfill components of solutions with significant scope and complexity. Lead quality assurance (QA) and user acceptance testing planning for developed solutions, and participates with business requestors in their user acceptance testing once QA testing is successfully completed. Develop test strategies, plans, and scripts and executes test procedures to ensure compliance of developed solution with documented specifications. Report test results to project stakeholders. Deliver training programs for IT and business personnel to ensure these standards, policies and procedures are well understood and adhered to by HPHC staff in accordance with regulatory requirements.
WHAT YOU NEED:


MA/MBA/MS or equivalent, plus 5 years experience, including a minimum of 3 years in health care data warehouse environment. Superior analytic problem-solving skills, including business process and data analytics. 

Data knowledge in finance or clinical side of insurance business; demonstrated ability to develop and deliver data analytic solutions of a complex nature. 

Demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously. Strong organizational skills, and the ability to prioritize multiple concurrent tasks. Strong verbal and written communication skills as well as negotiation skills. Team player, committed to quality process and outcomes. Demonstrated ability to lead teams and mentor junior data analysts. 

Proficient with PC’s; expertise in MS Office (MS Access, Word, Excel, Power Point, Visio, MS Project); sophisticated technical skills in SAS and SQL programming languages; Demonstrated understanding of principles of data modeling; Extract Transform Load (ETL) specifications; experience in database systems (Teradata, Oracle), as well as end-user analytic tools like MicroStrategy Web; Experience in MicroStrategy Web report development, understanding of its architecture and schema objects; Previous experience with documenting requirements, use cases, test cases, success criteria; Experience in Master Data Management. Ability to learn new technologies and applications quickly.

Name: Data Analyst
Description:
Position Objective:

Conduct data analysis and related functions in order to inform stakeholders, understand data trends, and tie data into business processes and objectives.

Duties and Responsibilities

Develop, update, and apply data models to generate reports and analysis to inform stakeholders.
Retrieve, validate, format, and organize a variety of data from many sources.
Conduct data analysis to answer standard or recurring inquiries and identify trends, correlation, and other relationships in data sets.
Work across various stakeholders to understand data trends, sources, and analysis goals and connect data to business processes to obtain a deeper understanding of potential considerations and assumptions.
Provide data integration by linking data from multiple sources to conduct organizational analysis.
Conduct detail oriented tasks and analysis projects independently with minimal supervision.
Create supporting materials for analysis projects (assumptions, briefings, handouts, written documents, user guides, etc.).
Development of metrics to identify trends in training and other integral data.

Basic Qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree in related field
At least four years of related experience in an office or professional setting
Secret Clearance

Minimum Qualifications:

Highly proficient in the MS Office Suite, particularly MS Excel.
Familiarity with software or tools used for business analytics, data analysis, and visualization such as Tableau, PowerPivot, PowerBI, Access, or Vizio.
Excellent data gathering and analytical skills.
Experience with data visualization methods and approaches.
Excellent oral and written communication skills.
Experience working with large data sets to distill information and present to all levels of organizational leadership.
Ability to interpret and analyze complex data, including sensitivity analyses, predictive analyses, and trends analyses.

Support internal Operations Team with client data verifications and ad hoc requests in an organized, clear, and timely fashion. Bachelor’s degree or equivalent; three to five years related experience and/or training; or equivalent combination of education and experience.

Plus, we work to maintain the best possible environment for our employees, where people can learn and grow with the company. We strive to provide a collaborative, creative environment where each person feels encouraged to contribute to our processes, decisions, planning and culture.

If you believe this is as important as we do, then AccessOne is the right place for you.

Name: Senior Data Analyst for Product Growth
Description:
As a Senior Data Analyst for Product Growth, you will:
Lead all things data for a growth team in our Product organization
Identify the drivers of activation, monetization, and engagement
Analyze large, rich data sets
Improve our product which helps 100,000+ developers build and deliver software faster
Build our product and growth analytics practice
About Product Growth Analytics at CircleCIWhat you'll do:
Be a brilliant analyst: Turn business problems into research plans. Leverage data from the data lake, data warehouse, third parties, and source systems. Work confidently with clean and messy data. Aggregate, clean, and explore. Soundly use statistics and probability. Tell compelling stories. Build impactful visualizations. Present insights to peers and executives. Drive action and outcomes. Turn repetitive analyses into dashboards.
Lead analytics for a product team: Partner with product managers. Brainstorm ideas, experiments, hypotheses, and roadmaps. Collaborate to fully understand context, needs, vision, and outcomes. Ask smart questions. Set team goals. Define, document, monitor and forecast KPI. Perform root cause analyses on key metrics. Define requirements for developers to improve data instrumentation.
Understand our product and customers: Analyze product features, journeys, and life cycles. Drive conversion, engagement, and efficiency across our funnel. Focus on activation, monetization, engagement, and retention. Identify customer characteristics and behaviors. Improve segmenting and cohorting.
Leverage a growth toolkit: Define the models, paths, and loops of growth. Identify and prioritize opportunities for incremental improvements. Work in cycles of build, measure, and learn. Define, implement, and interpret A/B tests and other experiments. Educate stakeholders on statistical validity. 

Build a growth practice: Scale success. Celebrate fast failure. Mature from one-off tactics to repeatable processes. Define best practices. Embrace not just quantitative, but qualitative; not just analytics, but creative thinking. Define requirements for data engineering to improve data, automation and analytics capabilities. 
What we're looking for:


Six years total of analytics experience with three years in Product or Growth: At least six years of analytics experience in total. At least three of those years in an analytics role specifically focused on product or growth.
Experience at a high-growth company: Analytics experience with high-growth businesses. Ideally, those with well-defined, product-enabled funnels and complex, high-volume customer flows.
Technical education: A bachelor's degree in a technical or quantitative field (e.g., Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering, Economics or Finance). A similar Master's degree is preferred.
Proficiency across analytics tools: Deep experience with analytical SQL queries (e.g., inner/left/right joins, CTEs, and window functions). Some experience with scripting within a notebook environment, preferably using Python, Pandas, and Jupyter. A desire to grow your modeling, machine-learning, and data-science skills. Familiarity with basic statistics (e.g., distributions, experiments, significance testing, and linear regression). Experience with a major analytics/visualization platform (e.g., Tableau or Looker). 

Proficiency across growth tools: Productive with growth tools. Specifically a product or events analytics platform (e.g., Google Analytics, Amplitude, Segment) and an AB testing tool (e.g., Optimizely, VWO). 
Bonus Points!
Passion for data, discover, and problem-solving
Curious; confident; open to questioning assumptions and being questioned.
Effective communicator across technical and business audiences. Able to manage stakeholder expectations and work with hands-on executives.
Entrepreneurial; fast-moving; able to balance vision and execution; and not easily discouraged. Instinct for value, and focused on the incremental.
