Name: Data Analyst
Description:
SUMMARY:ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS:
Establish and maintain foundational data
Design and build the data infrastructure necessary to support the implementation of Fiserv iVue in conjunction with the implementation of a new core - Fiserv DNA
Responsibility for systems administration, data architecture, reporting design & execution, and data controls.
Maintain and manage reporting platforms, ensuring reports are developed and distributed on time
Interpret data, analyze results using statistical techniques and provide ongoing reports
Develop and implement databases, data collection systems, data analytics and other strategies that optimize statistical efficiency and quality
Acquire data from primary or secondary data sources and maintain databases/data systems
Identify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets
Filter and "clean" data by reviewing computer reports, printouts, and performance indicators to locate and correct code problems
Work with management to prioritize business and information needs
Locate and define new process improvement opportunities
JOB REQUIREMENTS:
Bachelor's degree or equivalence required
Must have at least 3-5 years of database experience with advanced SAS and SQL skills; experience researching and manipulating complex and large data sets
Extensive experience building superior analytical and reporting tools and dashboards using data visualization, such as Tableau or Qlikview
Analytical thinker with superior data analysis skills; synthesizing information across multiple platforms, systems, and organizations
Proven working experience as a data analyst or business data analyst
Technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, data mining and segmentation techniques
Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy
Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings
KNOWLEDGE/SKILLS REQUIRED:
Excellent customer service skills
Strong communication skills, both verbal and written
High level of attention to detail, with strong problem solving & organizational skills
Must be able to operate in a self-directed manner with little direction; must have a strong desire to take the initiative to deliver superior results
Must have a high degree of attention to detail, specifically in ensuring all reports and underlying data are accurate
Ability to perform effectively in fast-paced environment
Working Knowledge of Microsoft Office, especially Excel
Complete all required compliance training by established deadlines
Ability to maintain confidentiality
PHYSICAL AND MENTAL QUALIFICATIONS:
Occasional standing, walking, bending and stooping required
Must be able to sit at a desk for long periods of time and use a computer

Name: Data Analyst
Description:
Job DescriptionOne of our top LA clients is looking for a Data Analyst to join their team, this is a newly created position! They are one of the largest hedge funds on the West Coast and are managing over $25B in assets. Technical Connections has staffed over half of their technology team in the past 15 years. The Data Management team is responsible for governance over trading related data including security attributes, position-level characteristics, and risk metrics.

Who are you?


You have at least two years of experience working for a hedge fund, fixed-income asset manager, investment bank, or financial technology company focused on capital markets.
You have a passion for all things data, you enjoy working closely with the trading floor, trading desk and compliance teams. You will also interface with Tech, portfolio management, fund accounting and regulatory reporting.
You are willing to take the time to learn how security attributes impact the departments listed above.
You have a Bachelor’s degree (or higher) from an accredited school, preferably a top school.
Financial products are something you are passionate about including bonds, structured products, loans, CDS, equities, options, etc.
Proficiency with Excel, or BI Tools, helpful to have experience with Bloomberg and SQL.

What’s in it for you?


An excellent leadership team who fosters growth, low turnover. Very stable company, have been in business for 25 years, free lunch, awesome Century City location, 100% paid medical benefits, competitive salary and bonus.

Note – Our client conducts and extensive background check including: Drug, Credit, Criminal, Education and Employment Verification.

We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.
